    <h1>UI Pattern Overview</h1>
    <h2>Interactive vs. Non-interactive Elements</h2>
    <p>Throughout the platform, <strong>we use 2px borders for non-interactive elements and 1px borders for interactive elements.</strong> The main non-interactive elements are Boxes, usually used to provide a page with structure. Interactive elements include buttons, form inputs, dropdowns, and so forth. Differentiating them visually will create an affordance of interactivity for any element with a 1px border.</p>
    <h3 class="u-mt-5">Interactive Element</h3>
    <input type="text" placeholder="Here is an input">
    <h3 class="u-mt-5">Non-interactive Element</h3>
    <section class="Box">
      <h3>Here is a headline</h3>
      <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nullam commodo ullamcorper sem non bibendum. Nunc sit amet tincidunt augue, nec commodo erat. Nam pulvinar, dui interdum condimentum interdum, felis risus tempor dui, quis volutpat tortor tellus vel quam.</p>
    </section>
    <div class="u-mt-6">
      <h2>Button Colors</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="small-6 columns u-mb-3">
          <div class="Box">
            <h3>Default</h3>
            <p>By default, buttons are grey. Any non-primary button should only have the <code>.Button</code> class.</p>
            <a href="#" class="Button u-mt-2">Default Button</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="small-6 columns u-mb-3">
          <div class="Box">
            <h3>Primary</h3>
            <p>The primary call to action on an element should have the additional class of <code>.Button--blue</code>.</p>
            <a href="#" class="Button Button--blue u-mt-2">Primary Button</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="small-6 columns">
          <div class="Box">
            <h3>Droplet Creation</h3>
            <p>There is a single green button in the UI, and it's reserved for Droplet creation.</p>
            <a href="#" class="Button Button--green u-mt-2">Creation Button</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="small-6 columns">
          <div class="Box">
            <h3>Destructive</h3>
            <p>Destructive actions should include the classes <code>.Button--red</code> and <code>.Button--outline</code>.</p>
            <a href="#" class="Button Button--red Button--outline u-mt-2">Destructive Button</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
